==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mahaled
<hw>Ma*ha"led</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[Ar.
<ets>mahled</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A cherry tree
(<spn>Prunus Mahaleb</spn>) of Southern Europe. The wood is prized by
cabinetmakers, the twigs are used for pipe stems, the flowers and leaves
yield a perfume, and from the fruit a violet dye and a fermented liquor
(like kirschwasser) are prepared.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

